title: Ceiling Border, 1875–1900
creditline: Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds
description:
Wallpaper roll.
Borders or sidewall: two different designs each occupying half the paper width. Stylized blue flowers on wavy background; and zig-zag motif with blue flowers. Printed in blue and metallic copper.
